48
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:12,360
They're throwing a party
even though they just moved in.

49
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,910
What is wrong with them?

50
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:14,960
It's so rowdy.

51
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,720
It's too rowdy.

52
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:18,360
Let me go and have a look.

53
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,440
Sure.

54
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:55,000
Mr. Shao.

55
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,670
What's going on?

56
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,750
I just moved here.

57
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,880
Please lower the volume of the music.

58
00:04:08,030 --> 00:04:08,830
Thank you.

59
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,830
Mr. Shao.

60
00:04:25,110 --> 00:04:26,270
What brought you here?

61
00:04:27,457 --> 00:04:27,881
Hi.

62
00:04:29,537 --> 00:04:30,051
Hi.

63
00:04:31,350 --> 00:04:32,070
How is it?

64
00:04:32,070 --> 00:04:33,230
Have you found a place?

65
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,270
I have,

66
00:04:35,350 --> 00:04:37,830
but you insisted on being the neighbor of An Yu.

67
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:39,390
What exactly do you want to do,

68
00:04:39,390 --> 00:04:40,160
Shao Moli?

69
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:43,230
Is this the right way to talk to your boss?

70
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,350
I've sent the photo of the house to you.

71
00:04:45,670 --> 00:04:47,350
Check it out yourself then.

72
00:04:50,550 --> 00:04:52,480
Unexpectedly, we've become Mr. Shao's neighbors.

73
00:04:52,550 --> 00:04:53,670
We're way too lucky.

74
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:54,600
Mr. Shao,

75
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:56,000
you just moved here?

76
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:57,550
Yes.

77
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,480
We just moved here.

78
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:00,600
You threw a party even though you just moved here?

79
00:05:00,790 --> 00:05:03,350
They're our clients.

80
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:05,950
They just came in abruptly to throw a party.

81
00:05:05,950 --> 00:05:07,070
I think it's very rowdy.

82
00:05:07,070 --> 00:05:08,320
So I'm out.

83
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:08,950
It's all right.

84
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:09,510
Perfect timing.

85
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,880
Take a rest here.

86
00:05:11,110 --> 00:05:12,390
We'll be neighbors in the future.

87
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:13,600
Let's visit each other more frequently.

88
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:15,230
What about I show you around?

89
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,270
Sure.

90
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:17,160
Come on.

91
00:05:19,830 --> 00:05:20,670
This

92
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:23,350
is our extremely huge washroom.

93
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:25,440
There are still some dirty clothes
which have yet to be washed.

94
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:27,000
Our washing machine has broken down.

95
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,480
I don't know when it can be repaired.

96
00:05:28,790 --> 00:05:29,640
This

97
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,950
is our kitchen.

98
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,510
I seem to be a bit hungry.

99
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:34,880
An'an,

100
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:35,720
are you hungry?

101
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:36,790
Let's order takeouts.

102
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:38,040
Sure.

103
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,760
Do you have any instant noodles?

104
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:42,510
Yes, we do.

105
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,480
Then let me cook the noodles.

106
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,600
It's very delicious.

107
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:11,950
Mr. Shao.

108
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,600
I didn't expect that you would be
not only handsome

109
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,760
but also capable.

110
00:06:14,830 --> 00:06:16,720
Unexpectedly, you know how to cook
such delicious food.

111
00:06:17,070 --> 00:06:18,880
I only know how to cook instant noodles.

112
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:19,510
That's enough.

113
00:06:20,110 --> 00:06:21,160
By the way, Lailai.

114
00:06:21,670 --> 00:06:24,350
I've done working on the balance sheet.

115
00:06:24,350 --> 00:06:25,600
You can double check later.

116
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,070
Okay.

117
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:28,160
There's no need to take a look at it.

118
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,760
It won't help the project.

119
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:33,670
And these are the financial statements
of Wei'er Hotel for ten years.

120
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:34,950
Each of us shall take half.

121
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:35,350
Okay.

122
00:06:35,350 --> 00:06:36,440
There's no need to take a look at these either.

123
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:37,600
They're unimportant.

124
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,160
It might seem to Mr. Shao

125
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,550
that we're wasting our time

126
00:06:42,550 --> 00:06:43,320
and that they're unimportant,

127
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:44,440
but to us,

128
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,350
they're very important.

129
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:46,270
Yes.

130
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:48,760
Moreover, these are related to whether
we can become permanent staff or not.

131
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:56,040
I just don't want to see you wasting your time

132
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,230
and energy.

133
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:58,950
Trust me.

134
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,510
A financial statement can't thoroughly reflect

135
00:07:00,510 --> 00:07:02,320
the actual situation of a company.

136
00:07:02,350 --> 00:07:04,040
You'll need to look into many different aspects

137
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:06,320
to truly understand a company.

138
00:07:15,510 --> 00:07:16,880
My goodness. I set three alarms.

139
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:18,160
I didn't expect that none of them woke me up.

140
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,880
I've heated milk and eggs.

141
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:22,440
Take them with you and eat
when you have a chance later.

142
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,320
Thank you, An'an.

143
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:25,760
It's our team leader.

144
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:27,880
Hello, Mr. Su.

145
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:29,920
I'm just out.

146
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:32,920
Okay, I'll go now.

147
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,320
Okay, bye-bye!

148
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,670
Our team leader wants me to go to the bank
to get some documents first

149
00:07:36,670 --> 00:07:37,270
before going to the company.

150
00:07:37,350 --> 00:07:38,320
You want to go to the bank first?

151
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:38,830
Yes.

152
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:39,550
Then I'll make a move first.

153
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:40,760
All right. Take a cab there then.

154
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:41,270
Sure.

155
00:07:41,390 --> 00:07:42,670
Thank you for your breakfast, An'an.

156
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:43,950
See you later at the company.

