00:08:37,570 --> 00:08:42,550
♪I'll continue running♪

172
00:08:43,170 --> 00:08:47,500
♪I wouldn't want to run away♪

173
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:51,520
[Zhuoyue Financial Group]

174
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:52,760
(To acquire Wei'er Hotel,)

175
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,320
we need to first understand

176
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,840
who exactly our competitor is.

177
00:08:57,080 --> 00:09:00,080
[Wei'er Hotel]
Rejection by the management is the most common

178
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:02,200
and very difficult problem faced
in an acquisition case.

179
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:04,110
So the first thing to settle after I got back

180
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:06,470
was to understand the willingness and attitude

181
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:09,150
of the management of Wei'er Hotel
towards our acquisition this time.

182
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,790
We were indeed quite lucky.

183
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:16,880
When I was still thinking
about who to approach to do so,

184
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:19,960
Chen Wei who loves throwing parties

185
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,030
[Chen Wei]
came to me uninvited.

186
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:34,520
Chen Wei revealed

187
00:09:34,590 --> 00:09:37,710
that there are two groups
in the management of Wei'er Hotel.

188
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,590
One of the groups comprises his underlings.

189
00:09:39,670 --> 00:09:41,150
As long as we can fulfill

190
00:09:41,150 --> 00:09:42,910
their requirements in respect
of their interests,

191
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,880
they'll then be willing to vote for us.

192
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,840
But the other group

193
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:48,200
is more difficult to deal with.

194
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:54,080
He Shuo.

195
00:09:54,350 --> 00:09:57,400
He's the only son of the founder
of Wei'er Hotel, He Shuhua.

196
00:09:57,470 --> 00:09:59,790
[He Shuo]
He's also one of the largest shareholders.

197
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,520
He's very clear in his stance

198
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,790
that he objects to our acquisition.

199
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,590
And he's not willing to negotiate with us.

200
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:07,030
In order to convince him,

201
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:07,880
we

202
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,880
will need to employ extraordinary means.

203
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:12,670
Mr. He,

204
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:15,320
this is the acquisition proposal

205
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:17,150
of Yimi Capital to Wei'er Hotel.

206
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:19,150
Please take a look.

207
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:20,590
There's no need.

208
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:23,520
We're not interested
in any of the acquisition proposals.

209
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,080
Mr. He.

210
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,030
Wei'er Hotel is currently

211
00:10:29,030 --> 00:10:30,520
facing serious financial stress.

212
00:10:31,110 --> 00:10:33,760
Introducing new capital is imperative.

213
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,080
You should be very clear
when you're in this industry.

214
00:10:37,230 --> 00:10:38,590
If your finance is not doing well,

215
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,080
things won't work.

216
00:10:41,230 --> 00:10:42,640
Moreover, as far as I'm aware,

217
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:45,280
Zhuoyue is also planning to acquire Wei'er Hotel.

218
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:47,550
No matter how dismissive you are of the plan,

219
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:49,520
you'll eventually need to choose

220
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:52,320
between Zhuoyue and Yimi.

221
00:10:52,670 --> 00:10:53,790
Yimi

222
00:10:54,110 --> 00:10:55,960
is surely your best choice.

223
00:10:56,670 --> 00:10:57,910
Why are you so confident?

224
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,880
Because I can offer a better price than Zhuoyue

225
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,550
before they actually offer a price.

226
00:11:05,150 --> 00:11:06,590
What you mean is

227
00:11:08,150 --> 00:11:09,840
that no matter what price Zhuoyue offers,

228
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:11,880
you'll have a way to know it.

229
00:11:13,350 --> 00:11:14,080
Of course.

230
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,520
I have my way.

231
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:19,710
Okay.

232
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,470
Then I'd like to see

233
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:23,470
how you're going to compete with Zhuoyue

234
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:24,640
in this round, Mr. Zhou.

235
00:12:09,910 --> 00:12:10,910
Is it delicious?

236
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,470
Eat more.

237
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:15,670
Mr. Shao.

238
00:12:16,590 --> 00:12:17,910
You're also feeding the cat?

239
00:12:18,710 --> 00:12:19,550
Yes.

240
00:12:19,790 --> 00:12:22,350
I see it wandering around the house these days.

241
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:24,110
I guessed it was a stray cat.

242
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:25,550
So I brought it some food.

243
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,440
There are some leftovers at home.

244
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:29,000
It seems

245
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,590
that it's enjoying better food now.

246
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:32,440
Why do you say so?

247
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:41,000
The weather is turning cold.

248
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:43,230
We need to figure out a way to make a den for it.

249
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:46,350
Eat more.

250
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,760
(With regard to the acquisition of Wei'er Hotel,)

251
00:12:59,790 --> 00:13:01,760
[Zhuoyue Financial Group]
(my proposal is to do our work from two aspects.)

252
00:13:02,150 --> 00:13:02,840
An Yu.

253
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:04,000
Since we're a team,

254
00:13:04,110 --> 00:13:05,640
share your proposal with everyone.

255
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:08,880
I think to successfully acquire Wei'er Hotel,

256
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:11,150
we'll need to understand the hotel's data.

257
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:16,790
I've created a table.

258
00:13:16,790 --> 00:13:18,640
This is a comparison of the hotel's data.

259
00:13:18,710 --> 00:13:21,230
We'll then know the sales status of the hotel,

260
00:13:21,230 --> 00:13:23,280
including its profit, liabilities, and more.

261
00:13:23,350 --> 00:13:25,150
These are all the bargaining chips.

262
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,400
At least we won't stay passive,

263
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:29,840
and we might have unexpected gains.

264
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,710
This is still just the first step.

265
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:34,670
I think what's more important

266
00:13:35,230 --> 00:13:37,320
is our strategy of acquiring Wei'er Hotel.

267
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:39,110
Does everyone still remember

268
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:42,960
the classic hungry lions game
in the Nash equilibrium?

269
00:13:45,590 --> 00:13:47,350
In order for everyone to understand it better,

270
00:13:47,470 --> 00:13:49,150
I prepared some props.

271
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:52,350
I hope that everyone can take part
in the role-playing game

272
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:55,200
to see this set of theories more intuitively.

273
00:13:55,350 --> 00:13:55,880
Lailai,

274
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:56,670
go and get the props then.

275
00:13:56,670 --> 00:13:57,280
I'm going.

276
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,760
In this set of theories,

277
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:04,550
we need six lions and one sheep.

